[
  {
    "function_v0": {
      "doc": "Initializes the LongShortPair contract.\\n\\nThis constructor is intended to be called exactly once at deploy time. It:\\n- Sets core admin roles (`Admin`, `PauseAdmin`, `EmergencyAdmin`) to `params.admin`\\n- Stores immutable-ish pair configuration such as the underlying `asset`\\n- Stores collateral configuration (`collateral_token`, `collateral_per_pair`)\\n- Stores token contract addresses for the LONG and SHORT tokens\\n- Stores oracle and calculator addresses\\n- Initializes price bounds (`lower_bound`, `upper_bound`)\\n\\n### Reverts\\n- [`LongShortPairError::AlreadyInitialized`] if the contract has already been initialized.\\n\\n### Arguments\\n- `e`: Soroban environment.\\n- `params`: Full set of pair parameters used to bootstrap the contract.",
      "name": "__constructor",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "params",
          "type_": {
            "udt": {
              "name": "PairParams"
            }
          }
        }
      ],
      "outputs": []
    }
  },
  {
    "function_v0": {
      "doc": "Mints equal amounts of LONG and SHORT tokens by depositing collateral.\\n\\nFor `tokens_to_mint`, the contract:\\n1. Calculates `collateral_used = tokens_to_mint * collateral_per_pair`\\n2. Transfers `collateral_used` of collateral from `user` into the Pair contract\\n3. Mints `tokens_to_mint` LONG and `tokens_to_mint` SHORT to the user\\n4. Increments the tracked `total_collateral`\\n\\nThis is the primary entry mechanism for creating new synthetic exposure.\\n\\n### Reverts\\n- [`LongShortPairError::InvalidInput`] if `tokens_to_mint == 0`.\\n- [`LongShortPairError::ActionPaused`] if minting is paused.\\n- [`LongShortPairError::MintingDisabled`] if the pair is not [`PairStatus::Active`].\\n\\n### Returns\\nReturns the amount of collateral transferred in (`collateral_used`).",
      "name": "mint",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "user",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "tokens_to_mint",
          "type_": "u128"
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        "u128"
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "function_v0": {
      "doc": "Redeems equal amounts of LONG and SHORT tokens for collateral.\\n\\nFor `tokens_to_redeem`, the contract:\\n1. Synchronizes internal collateral accounting (`sync_collateral`)\\n2. Burns `tokens_to_redeem` LONG and `tokens_to_redeem` SHORT from the user\\n3. Calculates `collateral_returned = tokens_to_redeem * collateral_per_pair`\\n4. Transfers `collateral_returned` of collateral back to the user\\n5. Decrements the tracked `total_collateral`\\n\\nThis redemption path requires burning *both* legs (LONG and SHORT) in equal quantity.\\n\\n### Reverts\\n- [`LongShortPairError::InvalidInput`] if `tokens_to_redeem == 0`.\\n- [`LongShortPairError::ActionPaused`] if redeeming is paused.\\n- [`LongShortPairError::InsufficientInventory`] if the contract does not have enough collateral.\\n\\n### Returns\\nReturns the amount of collateral returned (`collateral_returned`).",
      "name": "redeem",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "user",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "tokens_to_redeem",
          "type_": "u128"
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        "u128"
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "function_v0": {
      "doc": "Redeems a single side (LONG *or* SHORT) for collateral after expiration.\\n\\nThis method is only enabled when the pair status is [`PairStatus::Expired`]. At expiry,\\nsettlement determines the collateral split between LONG and SHORT using\\n`collateral_percent_long` (and `1 - collateral_percent_long` for SHORT).\\n\\nThe contract:\\n1. Synchronizes internal collateral accounting (`sync_collateral`)\\n2. Requires the pair to be expired\\n3. Determines the payout percent for `side`\\n4. Burns `tokens_to_redeem` of the chosen `side`\\n5. Pays out `tokens_to_redeem * collateral_per_pair * side_pct`\\n6. Decrements tracked `total_collateral`\\n\\n### Notes\\n- Redeeming a worthless side is forbidden (e.g., side percent is 0).\\n- A computed payout of 0 is rejected (e.g., tiny redemption amount).\\n\\n### Reverts\\n- [`LongShortPairError::InvalidInput`] if `tokens_to_redeem == 0` or payout would be 0.\\n- [`LongShortPairError::ActionPaused`] if redeeming is paused.\\n- [`LongShortPairError::InvalidStatus`] if the pair is not expired.\\n- [`LongShortPairErro",
      "name": "redeem_one",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "user",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "side",
          "type_": {
            "udt": {
              "name": "Side"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "tokens_to_redeem",
          "type_": "u128"
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        "u128"
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "function_v0": {
      "doc": "Updates the Pair's settlement allocation (`collateral_percent_long`) using the oracle TWAP.\\n\\nThis is a passthrough to `crate::utils::sync_collateral(&e)`.\\n\\nDespite the name, this does **not** transfer collateral or reconcile balances. It only:\\n- Queries the oracle TWAP\\n- Computes a new `collateral_percent_long` via the calculator\\n- Updates `last_update_ts` and `collateral_percent_long`\\n- Potentially marks the Pair as [`PairStatus::Expired`] and sets `expiration_ts`\\nif the TWAP reaches or crosses the configured bounds.\\n\\nThis function is useful for keepers/frontends that want to \\xe2\\x80\\x9cpoke\\xe2\\x80\\x9d the Pair so that\\nsettlement state is fresh before mint/redeem flows or UI display.",
      "name": "sync_collateral",
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": []
    }
  },
